{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Open embedding models let you run inference on your own hardware, eliminate per-token fees, and keep data private. The ecosystem has matured rapidly: models from BAAI, Alibaba, Nomic, and Mistral now match or beat proprietary APIs on the MTEB benchmark for many retrieval tasks, while remaining free to use under permissive licenses."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Open embedding model families, MTEB benchmark categories, and serving options including TEI and ONNX"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Open Model Families"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Four models dominate practical deployments, each with a distinct design philosophy:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dims"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Params"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "License"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key feature"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "BAAI/bge-m3"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1024"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "570M"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MIT"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dense + sparse + ColBERT in one model; 100+ languages"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Alibaba-NLP/gte-Qwen2-1.5B-instruct"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1536"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1.5B"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apache 2.0"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SOTA MTEB (2024); instruction-tuned; 32k context"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "768"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "137M"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apache 2.0"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Matryoshka + 8192-token context; fully open weights + training code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "intfloat/e5-mistral-7b-instruct"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4096"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "7B"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistral"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instruction-tuned LLM backbone; highest quality for complex queries"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The MTEB Benchmark"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Massive Text Embedding Benchmark evaluates models across 8 task categories and 56+ datasets. The categories span qualitatively different abilities:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Retrieval"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (15 datasets) — asymmetric: short query vs. long document. This is the primary signal for RAG."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (12 datasets) — embed → k-NN or linear probe; tests general semantic quality."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Clustering"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (11 datasets) — k-means on embeddings; tests topical coherence."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Semantic Textual Similarity"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (10 datasets) — symmetric: cosine distance vs. human judgements."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reranking"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (4 datasets), "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pair Classification"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (3), "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Summarization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (1), "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bitext Mining"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (26 multilingual datasets)."}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MTEB leaderboard rank is a starting point, not the final word. A model that ranks 5th overall may rank 1st on the specific domain and query length that matches your data. Always run a domain-specific eval before committing to a model."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Raw HuggingFace Transformers Usage"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For models not in sentence-transformers, or when you need more control over pooling, use the base HuggingFace API:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nfrom transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModel\n\nmodel_id = \"BAAI/bge-m3\"\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_id)\nmodel = AutoModel.from_pretrained(model_id)\nmodel.eval()\n\ndef embed(texts: list[str], batch_size: int = 32) -> torch.Tensor:\n    all_vecs = []\n    for i in range(0, len(texts), batch_size):\n        batch = texts[i : i + batch_size]\n        enc = tokenizer(\n            batch,\n            padding=True,\n            truncation=True,\n            max_length=8192,\n            return_tensors=\"pt\",\n        )\n        with torch.no_grad():\n            out = model(**enc)\n        # CLS token pooling — standard for BERT-style models\n        vecs = out.last_hidden_state[:, 0, :]        # shape (B, D)\n        vecs = F.normalize(vecs, p=2, dim=-1)        # unit-normalize\n        all_vecs.append(vecs)\n    return torch.cat(all_vecs, dim=0)\n\nvectors = embed([\"How does attention work?\", \"Transformers process tokens in parallel.\"])\nprint(vectors.shape)   # torch.Size([2, 1024])"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mean pooling (averaging all non-padding tokens) sometimes outperforms CLS pooling for models trained that way. Check the model card — bge-m3 and nomic use CLS; many sentence-transformers models use mean pooling internally."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def mean_pool(out, attention_mask) -> torch.Tensor:\n    # Mask padding tokens before averaging\n    token_vecs = out.last_hidden_state                       # (B, T, D)\n    mask = attention_mask.unsqueeze(-1).expand_as(token_vecs).float()\n    summed = (token_vecs * mask).sum(dim=1)\n    counts = mask.sum(dim=1).clamp(min=1e-9)\n    return F.normalize(summed / counts, p=2, dim=-1)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serving at Scale: HuggingFace TEI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For production workloads, running a model inside your application process is fragile — the model blocks the event loop, can't scale independently, and restarts take down the whole service. HuggingFace Text Embeddings Inference (TEI) is a purpose-built Rust server with continuous batching, Flash Attention, and a simple REST API."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# GPU server (requires NVIDIA driver)\ndocker run --gpus all \\\n  -p 8080:80 \\\n  -v $HOME/.cache/huggingface:/data \\\n  ghcr.io/huggingface/text-embeddings-inference:1.5 \\\n  --model-id BAAI/bge-m3 \\\n  --max-concurrent-requests 512\n\n# CPU-only server (no GPU required)\ndocker run -p 8080:80 \\\n  -v $HOME/.cache/huggingface:/data \\\n  ghcr.io/huggingface/text-embeddings-inference:cpu-1.5 \\\n  --model-id nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import httpx\n\nTEI_URL = \"http://localhost:8080\"\n\ndef embed_tei(texts: list[str]) -> list[list[float]]:\n    resp = httpx.post(\n        f\"{TEI_URL}/embed\",\n        json={\"inputs\": texts, \"normalize\": True},\n        timeout=30.0,\n    )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    return resp.json()  # list of float lists\n\n# OpenAI-compatible endpoint — works with any client using the OpenAI SDK\n# POST /v1/embeddings  {\"model\": \"bge-m3\", \"input\": [\"...\"]}\n# This means you can swap TEI for OpenAI with zero client code changes."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TEI exposes a Prometheus-compatible "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/metrics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " endpoint and a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/health"}, {"type": "text", "text": " readiness probe. Continuous batching means the server coalesces individual requests into GPU-efficient batches automatically — you do not need to batch on the client side, though batching still reduces HTTP overhead."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ONNX Export for CPU Inference"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPU access is not always available or cost-effective. ONNX Runtime with quantization makes 137M–570M parameter models fast enough for real-time CPU inference."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pip install optimum[onnxruntime]\n\n# Export and quantize to INT8 (roughly 4x smaller, 2-3x faster on CPU)\noptimum-cli export onnx \\\n  --model nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5 \\\n  --optimize O2 \\\n  --task feature-extraction \\\n  ./nomic-onnx/"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from optimum.onnxruntime import ORTModelForFeatureExtraction\nfrom transformers import AutoTokenizer\nimport torch, torch.nn.functional as F\n\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"./nomic-onnx\")\nort_model = ORTModelForFeatureExtraction.from_pretrained(\"./nomic-onnx\")\n\ndef embed_onnx(texts: list[str]) -> list[list[float]]:\n    enc = tokenizer(texts, padding=True, truncation=True,\n                    max_length=8192, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n    with torch.no_grad():\n        out = ort_model(**enc)\n    vecs = out.last_hidden_state[:, 0, :]  # CLS pooling\n    vecs = F.normalize(vecs, p=2, dim=-1)\n    return vecs.tolist()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choosing a Serving Strategy"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "sentence-transformers in-process"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — best for scripts, notebooks, and low-traffic batch jobs. Zero operational overhead; simple to debug."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ONNX + ORTModel"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — best when you need faster-than-PyTorch CPU inference inside an existing service without adding a sidecar."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "HuggingFace TEI (CPU or GPU)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — best for any production API. Continuous batching, horizontal scaling, OpenAI-compatible endpoint, Prometheus metrics."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Raw transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — only when you need custom pooling, multi-vector output (ColBERT), or models not supported by sentence-transformers."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Licensing and Practical Notes"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MIT and Apache 2.0 licenses (bge-m3, GTE-Qwen2, nomic) impose no restrictions on commercial use. The e5-mistral-7b model inherits the Mistral base model license — review it if deploying commercially. Always check the model card on HuggingFace; some models restrict use for training competing embedding models."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model weights are large: nomic at 548 MB, bge-m3 at 2.3 GB, GTE-Qwen2-1.5B at ~3 GB, e5-mistral at ~14 GB. HuggingFace Hub caches downloads to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "~/.cache/huggingface/hub"}, {"type": "text", "text": " by default. Set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "HF_HOME"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to redirect to a larger volume in containerized environments."}]}]}}